race.comment: LONHRO'S SHADOW (8) is another decent winning chance for the McEvoy stable. Jumped out well and was heavily backed first-up, beaten 1.7L at Colac. Will have taken fitness and learning from that and in a positive switch Coffey rides today and will give her every chance from an inside barrier. DANCE LADY (10) disappointed at Kyneton but just missed at Swan Hill first-up off a positive Flemington jumpout. Third-up now and this suits a lot better. KOVU (2) resumes and has shown enough to consider if presented on song. Placed in a recent jumpout and gets in well with the 3kg claim. Should be around the mark with a good ride. PHILHARMONIC (5) debuts and placed in a recent jumpout. Hill sticks from that and he deserves a betting watch. FARM HORSE (3) jumps from an inside gate and is a likely improver from the Dwyer yard.
